race.comment: ESMAHLI (10) is in a top metro barn and impressed when comfortably winning his Maiden here as a $3.4 favourite. The gate is a little awkward, but 21% stable-striker Dee rides today and the colt is capable of taking the next step. ROSA AOTEAROA (9) raced as a short-priced favourite and led and won his Maiden here by 5L. Just missed from the front at Ballarat after that and is on a 7-day return. He will be tough to beat. THUNDER AWARD (5) will give away a start but is busting to win again and can make the finish with average luck. RUSSIAN FRONT (4) brings an easy 56 win from Kyneton and maps well. He's also in the mix.
